## Component installs

- Use the latest Shadcn CLI when adding new components.

## UI and map stability

- Keep E2E interactions deterministic; avoid wheel/drag map interactions in tests.
- Preserve user map view unless the feature explicitly focuses results.
- Keep highlighted IDs stable across Plotly refreshes.

## Persistence limits

- Avoid storing large Plotly payloads in localStorage.
